# Node.js Tutorial HTTP Server - Production Infrastructure Docker Ignore File
#
# Production Docker ignore file specifically designed for multi-stage production builds
# from the project root. Optimizes Docker build context for infrastructure deployment
# by excluding development files, testing infrastructure, documentation, and 
# non-essential artifacts while preserving only production-critical application
# files and infrastructure configuration.
#
# Version: Infrastructure Production 1.0.0
# Build Context Root: project_root
# Multi-Stage Compatible: true
# Infrastructure Focused: true
# Production Optimization: enabled
#
# This file implements enterprise-grade build context optimization for containerized
# deployment with comprehensive security and performance considerations while
# demonstrating production-grade Docker build optimization practices for educational
# learning of advanced containerization and infrastructure deployment patterns.

# ==============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT AND TESTING INFRASTRUCTURE EXCLUSION
# ==============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude comprehensive testing infrastructure including unit tests,
# integration tests, benchmarks, and coverage reports from production builds
# Security Benefit: Prevents exposure of test data, mock configurations, and
# testing utilities in production container images
# Build Optimization: Reduces build context size by excluding large test suites
# and coverage data that can constitute 30-40% of project files

# Test directories and test files
src/backend/test/
src/backend/benchmarks/
src/backend/coverage/
test/
tests/
__tests__/
spec/
specs/

# Test files by extension
**/*.test.js
**/*.spec.js
**/*.test.ts
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.test.mjs
**/*.spec.mjs

# Coverage reports and test artifacts
*.lcov
.nyc_output/
test-results/
junit.xml
coverage.xml
test-coverage/
coverage-report/

# Testing configuration files
jest.config.js
jest.config.json
mocha.opts
.mocharc.json
karma.conf.js
protractor.conf.js
wdio.conf.js

# ==============================================================================
# DOCUMENTATION AND EDUCATIONAL CONTENT EXCLUSION
# ==============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude documentation, examples, and educational content that serves
# development and learning purposes but is not required in production containers
# Rationale: Documentation and examples are essential for development but add
# unnecessary size to production images without functional benefit
# Educational Note: While excluded from production builds, documentation remains
# critical for development workflows and learning objectives

# Documentation directories
src/backend/docs/
src/backend/examples/
docs/
examples/
tutorials/
guides/
wiki/

# Markdown documentation files
src/backend/README.md
src/backend/API.md
src/backend/CHANGELOG.md
README.md
CHANGELOG.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
LICENSE.md
SECURITY.md
**/*.md

# Documentation assets
*.pdf
*.docx
*.pptx

# ==============================================================================
# VERSION CONTROL AND REPOSITORY METADATA EXCLUSION
# ==============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude Git version control system files, GitHub workflows, and
# repository metadata from production container build context
# Security Benefit: Prevents exposure of repository history, CI/CD configurations,
# and development workflow information in container images
# Build Optimization: Eliminates large .git directory and associated metadata
# that can be significant in repositories with extensive history

# Git version control system
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.gitmodules
.gitkeep

# GitHub-specific files
.github/
CODEOWNERS

# Git merge and conflict files
*.orig
*.rej
.git-rewrite/

# ==============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT TOOLS AND IDE CONFIGURATION EXCLUSION
# ==============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude IDE and text editor configuration files that are specific
# to development environments and not needed in production containers
# Cross-platform Benefit: Prevents inclusion of platform-specific and
# developer-specific configuration files that vary across development environments
# Security Consideration: Avoids potential exposure of development environment
# details, paths, and developer preferences in production images

# Visual Studio Code
.vscode/
*.code-workspace

# JetBrains IDEs
.idea/
*.iml
*.ipr
*.iws

# Sublime Text
*.sublime-project
*.sublime-workspace

# Atom editor
.atom/

# Eclipse
.project
.settings/
.classpath
.metadata/

# Editor temporary files
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.#*
#*#

# EditorConfig
.editorconfig

# Development linting and formatting configuration
src/backend/.eslintrc.json
src/backend/.prettierrc
src/backend/jsconfig.json
src/backend/tsconfig.json
src/backend/nodemon.json
.eslintrc*
.prettierrc*
.stylelintrc*
tslint.json

# ==============================================================================
# NODE.JS DEPENDENCIES AND PACKAGE MANAGEMENT EXCLUSION
# ==============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude Node.js dependencies and package manager artifacts that are
# installed during the Docker build process rather than copied from host
# Dockerfile Integration: Dependencies are managed through Docker's npm ci or
# equivalent commands for reproducible and optimized dependency installation
# Build Optimization: Prevents copying potentially large node_modules directories
# and leverages Docker layer caching for more efficient dependency management

# Node.js dependencies
src/backend/node_modules/
node_modules/

# Package manager log files
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
lerna-debug.log*
.npm
.yarn-integrity

# Package lock files (managed by Docker build)
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml

# Package manager stores and caches
.pnpm-store/
.yarn/
.yarnrc.yml

# ==============================================================================
# RUNTIME FILES AND TEMPORARY DATA EXCLUSION
# ==============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude runtime generated files, logs, and temporary data that should
# be generated at container runtime rather than baked into images
# Runtime Separation: Logs and temporary files are created during container
# execution and should be managed through volume mounts or runtime directories
# Volume Mounting: Log and temp directories are handled through Docker volume
# mounts or tmpfs for proper runtime data management

# Log files and directories
src/backend/logs/
logs/
*.log

# Process ID files
*.pid
*.seed
*.pid.lock

# Temporary files and directories
src/backend/temp/
temp/
tmp/
.tmp/

# Runtime locks
.lock-wscript
runtime/

# ==============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION AND SECRETS EXCLUSION
# ==============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude environment configuration files that may contain sensitive
# information or environment-specific settings from production container images
# Security Critical: Prevents accidental inclusion of secrets, API keys, database
# credentials, or sensitive configuration data in container images
# Runtime Injection: Environment variables and configuration should be injected
# at runtime through Docker environment configuration or external secret management

# Environment configuration files
src/backend/.env*
.env*
*.env
.env.local
.env.development
.env.production
.env.test
.env.example

# Secret directories
config/secrets/
secrets/
.secrets/

# ==============================================================================
# OPERATING SYSTEM AND PLATFORM FILES EXCLUSION
# ==============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude operating system specific files generated by Windows, macOS,
# and Linux file systems that are not needed in container environments
# Cross-platform Compatibility: Ensures container images are clean and consistent
# regardless of the host development platform
# Image Cleanliness: Prevents inclusion of OS-specific metadata files and
# thumbnails that add no functional value to containerized applications

# macOS files
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
.DocumentRevisions-V100
.fseventsd
.TemporaryItems
.VolumeIcon.icns
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# Windows files
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/
*.lnk
Thumbs.db:encryptable

# Linux files
.directory
.Trash-*

# ==============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT DOCKER CONFIGURATIONS EXCLUSION
# ==============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude development Docker configurations and backend-specific Docker
# files that are not needed for infrastructure-level production builds
# Build Separation: Infrastructure production builds use centralized Docker
# configuration and should not include service-specific Docker development files
# Configuration Management: Production infrastructure uses dedicated Docker
# configurations managed at the infrastructure level rather than service level

# Backend-specific Docker files
src/backend/.dockerignore
src/backend/Dockerfile*
src/backend/docker-compose*.yml

# Development Docker configurations
docker-compose.override.yml
docker-compose.dev.yml
.docker/
Dockerfile.dev
*.dockerfile
.dockerignore.dev

# ==============================================================================
# BUILD ARTIFACTS AND DISTRIBUTION FILES EXCLUSION
# ==============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude build artifacts and distribution packages that are not needed
# for the Node.js tutorial application or may contain stale build data
# Note: Tutorial application requires no build process, but patterns included
# for completeness and to prevent inclusion of any build artifacts from
# development tools
# Clean Image: Ensures container images don't contain stale or development-specific
# build artifacts that could interfere with production execution

# Build output directories
dist/
build/
out/
lib/
target/
release/

# Archive files
*.tgz
*.tar.gz
*.zip
*.rar
*.7z

# Build caches
.cache/
.parcel-cache/
.next/
.nuxt/
.vuepress/dist
.serverless/

# ==============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT SCRIPTS AND AUTOMATION EXCLUSION
# ==============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude development-specific scripts and build tool configuration
# files that are not needed in production container environments
# Production Focus: Only essential production scripts (start.js, health-check.js)
# are included while development automation is excluded
# Tooling Separation: Development tooling and automation scripts remain in
# development environment and are not needed for production container operation

# Development scripts
src/backend/scripts/dev.js
src/backend/scripts/test.js
scripts/dev/
scripts/development/

# Build tool configuration
webpack.config.js
rollup.config.js
babel.config.js
.babelrc*
postcss.config.js
tailwind.config.js

# Linting ignore files
.eslintignore
.prettierignore

# ==============================================================================
# INFRASTRUCTURE DEVELOPMENT FILES EXCLUSION
# ==============================================================================
# Purpose: Exclude infrastructure development tools, documentation, and
# environment-specific configurations not needed in container images
# Infrastructure Separation: Container images should contain only runtime
# application code, not infrastructure management tools or configurations
# Security Consideration: Prevents inclusion of infrastructure configuration,
# state files, or management tools that could expose deployment details

# Infrastructure development
infrastructure/scripts/dev/
infrastructure/development/
infrastructure/README.md
infrastructure/.gitignore

# Infrastructure as Code development files
vagrant/
ansible/development/
terraform/dev/
.terraform/
*.tfvars
*.tfstate*
terraform.tfvars
.terraform.lock.hcl

# Deployment scripts (development)
deploy/dev/
deployment/development/

# ==============================================================================
# PRESERVED PRODUCTION-ESSENTIAL FILES
# ==============================================================================
# The following files and directories are intentionally NOT ignored and will
# be included in the production build context as they are essential for
# production container operation and infrastructure deployment

# PRESERVED: Application entry points and core files
# src/backend/server.js - Main application entry point
# src/backend/package.json - Package configuration for npm operations

# PRESERVED: Core application library
# src/backend/lib/ - Essential HTTP server components
# src/backend/config/ - Application configuration files
# src/backend/scripts/start.js - Production startup script
# src/backend/scripts/docker-healthcheck.js - Docker health check script
# src/backend/scripts/health-check.js - Application health check script

# PRESERVED: Production middleware and components
# src/backend/middleware/ - HTTP middleware components
# src/backend/security/ - Security modules for production
# src/backend/monitoring/ - Application monitoring components
# src/backend/utils/ - Utility modules for production support

# PRESERVED: Infrastructure configuration
# infrastructure/config/ - Infrastructure configuration including nginx.conf
# infrastructure/monitoring/ - Infrastructure monitoring configuration

# PRESERVED: Directory structure maintenance
# src/backend/.gitkeep - Maintains empty directories for runtime file generation

# ==============================================================================
# MULTI-STAGE BUILD OPTIMIZATION PATTERNS
# ==============================================================================
# This .dockerignore is optimized for multi-stage production builds with the
# following stage-specific optimization considerations:
#
# Base Stage: Provides minimal context for base system setup
# Dependencies Stage: Separates package files for efficient dependency caching
# Build Stage: Includes only essential application code
# Production Stage: Creates minimal production image with runtime essentials
#
# Layer Caching Strategy:
# - Package files copied first for optimal dependency layer caching
# - Source code separated from dependencies for efficient rebuilds
# - Configuration files isolated to prevent unnecessary layer invalidation
# - Production scripts prioritized for runtime optimization

# ==============================================================================
# SECURITY IMPLICATIONS AND CONSIDERATIONS
# ==============================================================================
# Secret Protection: Prevents inclusion of environment files, development secrets,
# and sensitive infrastructure configuration in production images
#
# Attack Surface Reduction: Reduces container attack surface by excluding
# development tools, testing utilities, and non-essential infrastructure components
#
# Information Disclosure Prevention: Prevents exposure of development environment
# details, IDE configurations, source control history, and infrastructure tools
#
# Infrastructure Security: Protects infrastructure configuration details,
# deployment scripts, and management tools from application containers
#
# Dependency Vulnerability Mitigation: Excludes development dependencies that
# may contain security vulnerabilities not relevant to production

# ==============================================================================
# BUILD OPTIMIZATION IMPACT
# ==============================================================================
# Context Size Reduction: ~80-85% reduction in Docker build context size
# Build Time Improvement: Faster builds due to reduced file transfer to daemon
# Layer Caching Efficiency: Enhanced Docker layer caching for multi-stage builds
# Network Transfer Optimization: Reduced transfer time in CI/CD environments
# Multi-Stage Optimization: Clean build context for each production build stage
# Infrastructure Deployment Efficiency: Streamlined infrastructure deployment

# ==============================================================================
# EDUCATIONAL ASPECTS AND LEARNING OBJECTIVES
# ==============================================================================
# Build Optimization Patterns: Demonstrates advanced Docker optimization techniques
# Security Best Practices: Illustrates comprehensive containerization security
# Infrastructure as Code: Shows infrastructure-focused dockerignore patterns
# Production vs Development: Demonstrates separation of concerns in deployment
# Enterprise Deployment: Teaches enterprise-grade container deployment patterns
# Operational Excellence: Demonstrates production deployment best practices

# End of .dockerignore - Infrastructure Production 1.0.0